Steps:

	1A) Asynchronous query is made to Flickr API for images tagged with that search term.
		-Input bar is cleared
		-View adds <p>Search for Instagram photos tagged with "cats"</p>

2) Images are displayed in the html
	ng-repeat

3) There is text telling the user how many images were found
	Animate this text - have it pulsate/glow - whatever.

4) If no images found, text should reflect this.

5) If there was an error calling to the server, then there should be a message indicating this to the user.	
